SIMPLE: unshot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unshot
<hw>Un*shot"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>shot</ets>.]</ety> <def>To remove the shot from,
as from a shotted gun; to unload.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unshot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unshot
<hw>Un*shot"</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> +
<ets>shot</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not hit by a shot; also, not discharged or
fired off.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unshout</ent>⟦br⟧
